28/07/2003
POREC, Croatia -- Prime Minister Ivica Racan and President Stipe Mesic have signed a plan framing the work of the national intelligence services next year. During a visit to Istria County on Saturday (26 July), Racan said the document makes the fight against terrorism, organised crime and corruption a priority. He noted that this marks the first time that a prime minister and president of Croatia have jointly formulated directives for the intelligence services and presented them to the public. (MediaScan - 28/07/03; HINA, BBC - 26/07/03)
